Jenna Etheridge, News24(Supplied by ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A cyclist was killed in an alleged hit and run in Ladysmith on Thursday evening, Kwazulu Natal paramedics said.The man, believed to be in his thirties, had been cycling on a gravel road, said ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall. Paramedics found him in a critical condition at around 18:00 and immediately started cardiopulmonary resuscitation. He was transported to Ladysmith Provincial Hospital and declared dead after CPR was terminated. Police would investigate the circumstances of his death. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.